{"id":25163,"date":"2017-08-14T13:19:23","date_gmt":"2017-08-14T09:19:23","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=25163"},"modified":"2023-09-28T11:35:00","modified_gmt":"2023-09-28T07:35:00","slug":"waswas-angels-devils","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/08\/14\/waswas-angels-devils\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Waswas: Angels suggest good, devils suggest evil"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Verily, Satan influences the son of Adam and so does the angel. As for the influence of Satan, he threatens evil and denies the truth. As for the influence of the angel, he promises goodness and affirms the truth. Whoever finds this goodness, let him know it is from Allah, and let him praise Allah. Whoever finds something else, let him seek refuge in Allah from the accursed Satan.<\/strong>\u201d Then, the Prophet recited the verse, \u201c<strong>Satan threatens you with poverty and commands evil, but Allah promises you forgiveness and grace from Him<\/strong>.\u201d (2:268)<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2988<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <i>Hasan <\/i>(fair) according to Al-Tirmidhi<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0639\u064f\u0648\u062f\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0644\u0650\u0644\u0634\u0651\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0637\u064e\u0627\u0646\u0650 \u0644\u064e\u0645\u0651\u064e\u0629\u064b \u0628\u0650\u0627\u06